div1.p:
JOHN SOMMERVILLE. In June last I was churchwarden of St. Pancras, Soper-lane;
Ralph Lake Venables
was a pensioner on the parish at 6 s. a week, which was generally paid every month. The prisoner presented himself on the 25th of June to receive Venables's money, and said his name was Jackson; he said Venables was very ill. Igave him 1 l. 4 s., and told him next time he came to bring a certificate of his health.
